This article is a Presidential Memorandum from July 19, 2012, titled "Ensuring the Uniformed Services Employment and Reemployment Rights Act (USERRA) Protections." The memorandum emphasizes the importance of protecting the employment rights of individuals who have served in the uniformed services and outlines steps for federal agencies to improve compliance with USERRA. The memorandum establishes the USERRA Employment Protection Working Group, which will coordinate and review agency efforts to implement USERRA. It also directs the Office of Personnel Management to issue guidance to agencies on USERRA employment protection and to review relevant statutes, regulations, policies, and agency training and guidance to identify reforms that would strengthen USERRA protections. The memorandum further instructs agencies to prioritize policies and actions to implement USERRA employment protections and allocate sufficient resources for their implementation. The memorandum concludes with general provisions and encourages independent agencies to comply with its requirements.